01:31:05,475 --> 01:31:07,807
Um... are you OK?

614
01:31:14,317 --> 01:31:15,750
Breakdown?

615
01:31:18,121 --> 01:31:19,213
Yeah

616
01:31:19,555 --> 01:31:20,920
Want some?

617
01:31:31,300 --> 01:31:32,198
You are?

618
01:31:34,070 --> 01:31:35,401
Oh, me? Um...

619
01:31:38,007 --> 01:31:39,668
What are you doing here?

620
01:31:42,812 --> 01:31:44,677
What am I doing here...?

621
01:31:47,583 --> 01:31:48,641
You?

622
01:31:56,259 --> 01:31:57,624
So neither your dad nor your mom

623
01:31:57,760 --> 01:32:01,127
made it through...

624
01:32:01,764 --> 01:32:02,924
No...

625
01:32:04,133 --> 01:32:07,159
So many things happened at once,

626
01:32:07,470 --> 01:32:09,802
it's impossible to sort them all out

627
01:32:11,240 --> 01:32:12,229
Yeah

628
01:32:15,611 --> 01:32:19,206
Me too. My head's all messed up

629
01:32:21,384 --> 01:32:23,614
So you're a student, Kawashima?

630
01:32:23,753 --> 01:32:24,651
Yeah

631
01:32:26,022 --> 01:32:27,011
Lucky you

632
01:32:27,490 --> 01:32:28,787
I don't think so

633
01:32:29,325 --> 01:32:30,349
Here

634
01:32:31,060 --> 01:32:32,152
Oh, thanks...

635
01:32:35,598 --> 01:32:36,622
And you?

636
01:32:37,433 --> 01:32:38,764
I had a job

637
01:32:39,836 --> 01:32:41,064
Wow, amazing

638
01:32:41,337 --> 01:32:42,599
Nothing amazing

639
01:32:46,609 --> 01:32:48,042
Did you have any friends?

640
01:32:48,911 --> 01:32:50,037
Friends?

641
01:32:53,082 --> 01:32:54,481
Maybe one, I guess

642
01:32:55,418 --> 01:32:56,510
What was she like?

643
01:33:00,423 --> 01:33:02,084
What? I don't really know...

644
01:33:04,427 --> 01:33:06,691
I never really found out...

645
01:33:07,296 --> 01:33:08,456
Where is she?

646
01:33:09,699 --> 01:33:11,030
Somewhere...

647
01:33:14,370 --> 01:33:15,997
OK, try starting it

648
01:33:27,884 --> 01:33:29,681
OK, good

649
01:33:47,169 --> 01:33:48,158
Why don't you look for her?

650
01:33:49,105 --> 01:33:50,094
What?

651
01:33:51,440 --> 01:33:55,274
She's still somewhere, right?
You've got to help her then

652
01:33:57,446 --> 01:33:58,777
But...

653
01:33:59,882 --> 01:34:02,942
Let's go find her. I'll help you

654
01:34:09,692 --> 01:34:11,990
This is the last stop...

655
01:34:17,266 --> 01:34:21,032
After that we go as far as we can

656
01:34:25,408 --> 01:34:28,775
I can sort of see...

657
01:34:29,979 --> 01:34:31,139
The future...

658
01:34:41,591 --> 01:34:45,118
"Help"

659
01:35:08,618 --> 01:35:10,347
Look over there

660
01:35:13,522 --> 01:35:15,353
An abandoned factory?

661
01:35:22,498 --> 01:35:24,261
I wonder...

662
01:35:27,269 --> 01:35:28,497
Shall we try it?

663
01:35:47,223 --> 01:35:50,715
Listen, even if you see
a door sealed with red tape,

664
01:35:50,926 --> 01:35:53,292
don't go near it, OK?

665
01:35:54,096 --> 01:35:55,495
I know

666
01:36:19,922 --> 01:36:21,048
You OK?

667
01:37:01,130 --> 01:37:03,257
Look... at this

668
01:37:13,275 --> 01:37:14,674
Look... over there

669
01:37:41,203 --> 01:37:42,500
Kawashima

670
01:37:42,638 --> 01:37:43,764
Harue!

671
01:37:44,240 --> 01:37:45,366
Watch out!

672
01:37:47,710 --> 01:37:49,268
What happened, Harue!

673
01:37:50,279 --> 01:37:52,611
What are you doing with that?

674
01:37:56,819 --> 01:38:00,220
Let's get out of this place together

675
01:38:03,225 --> 01:38:04,556
Together?

676
01:38:05,561 --> 01:38:06,789
Yeah

677
01:38:20,109 --> 01:38:21,303
C'mon, hand it over

678
01:38:21,477 --> 01:38:23,069
Harue! Harue!

679
01:38:25,915 --> 01:38:29,851
Oh, no, a hospital...

680
01:38:42,431 --> 01:38:45,059
Harue! Don't die!

681
01:38:45,234 --> 01:38:47,065
C'mon! Please!

682
01:38:48,737 --> 01:38:50,034
Help me!

683
01:38:52,975 --> 01:38:55,466
Harue!

684
01:39:07,923 --> 01:39:09,447
We couldn't save her...

685
01:39:12,261 --> 01:39:13,193
No...

686
01:39:37,486 --> 01:39:39,044
We're out of gas...

687
01:39:40,956 --> 01:39:43,618
I'll get some,
there was gas back there

688
01:39:43,993 --> 01:39:45,153
You'll be OK?

689
01:39:45,961 --> 01:39:47,519
Wait for me. I'll be OK

690
01:41:45,547 --> 01:41:47,310
Forever...

691
01:41:49,351 --> 01:41:50,875
death was...

692
01:41:51,086 --> 01:41:53,577
eternal Ioneliness...

693
01:42:02,731 --> 01:42:09,637
Help...

694
01:42:10,005 --> 01:42:13,771
Don't ask me!
What's that got to do with me!

695
01:42:15,277 --> 01:42:17,108
Forever...

696
01:42:17,746 --> 01:42:19,577
death was...

697
01:42:20,382 --> 01:42:21,872
eternal Ioneliness...

698
01:42:29,858 --> 01:42:31,883
You're not real

699
01:42:33,295 --> 01:42:36,287
I refuse to acknowledge... Never...

700
01:42:37,166 --> 01:42:39,532
I refuse to acknowledge death!

701
01:43:24,313 --> 01:43:25,837
I know

702
01:43:27,349 --> 01:43:29,283
I'll catch you

703
01:43:29,918 --> 01:43:32,045
Then you'll disappear

704
01:43:33,388 --> 01:43:35,879
That's it, right? Right?

705
01:43:36,859 --> 01:43:39,020
You can't beat me!

706
01:44:08,524 --> 01:44:10,492
I am...

707
01:44:12,928 --> 01:44:15,488
real...

708
01:46:09,978 --> 01:46:11,536
Kawashima!

709
01:46:18,787 --> 01:46:20,118
What is it?

710
01:46:20,255 --> 01:46:22,883
Forget it... Let's go...

711
01:48:38,059 --> 01:48:40,391
It's too much...

712
01:48:52,174 --> 01:48:56,167
What... are you doing?

713
01:49:01,716 --> 01:49:04,913
You went in there...

714
01:49:06,988 --> 01:49:08,182
Me?

715
01:49:10,125 --> 01:49:12,286
Yeah, I did, but I'm fine

716
01:49:27,776 --> 01:49:29,437
Don't cry

717
01:49:53,034 --> 01:49:54,296
You want to go back?

718
01:49:55,871 --> 01:49:57,600
To what's left of Harue?

719
01:50:03,912 --> 01:50:05,402
That makes you feel better?

720
01:50:11,286 --> 01:50:14,744
If that's what you want,
I'll go with you

721
01:50:18,593 --> 01:50:19,855
No...

722
01:50:21,329 --> 01:50:22,660
Let's go...

723
01:50:23,532 --> 01:50:25,466
As far as we can go

724
01:50:30,305 --> 01:50:31,966
Are you sure about that?

725
01:50:38,547 --> 01:50:39,844
Yeah

726
01:50:58,333 --> 01:50:59,891
Can you get out?

727
01:51:07,309 --> 01:51:08,469
You OK?

728
01:51:21,256 --> 01:51:22,484
Be careful

729
01:51:33,435 --> 01:51:34,493
Wait here, OK?

730
01:52:49,911 --> 01:52:53,210
Death comes to us all...

731
01:52:54,015 --> 01:52:57,951
If so, maybe we would
have been happier,

732
01:52:58,086 --> 01:52:59,986
had we gone with the rest

733
01:53:01,056 --> 01:53:04,719
But we chose to keep going

734
01:53:05,026 --> 01:53:07,722
into the future...

735
01:53:26,948 --> 01:53:29,348
We'll head for Latin America

736
01:53:29,751 --> 01:53:32,413
We're still getting signals there

737
01:53:33,288 --> 01:53:34,721
Though they're pretty weak

738
01:53:36,624 --> 01:53:38,421
We've got to give it a try,

739
01:53:40,061 --> 01:53:41,426
no matter what we find

740
01:53:45,066 --> 01:53:46,658
If anyone's survived,

741
01:53:46,868 --> 01:53:48,460
we can head out again

742
01:53:48,670 --> 01:53:50,001
and go...

743
01:53:53,007 --> 01:53:54,736
as far as we can

744
01:54:03,785 --> 01:54:07,050
C'mon, be strong

745
01:54:11,092 --> 01:54:14,528
Have I done the right thing?

746
01:54:16,598 --> 01:54:17,587
Yes

747
01:54:18,700 --> 01:54:19,894
Are you sure?

748
01:54:20,668 --> 01:54:21,760
Yes

749
01:54:22,203 --> 01:54:25,138
You're doing the right thing

750
01:55:02,410 --> 01:55:06,437
Now, alone with
my last friend in the world,

751
01:55:07,348 --> 01:55:09,509
I have found happiness

